observations.recommendation:
We recommended that Management instruct:

The Inventory Committee to conduct an inventory of the local roads under the jurisdiction of the municipality and render a Report on the Physical count of the Road Networks System;

The Acting Municipal Treasurer (where no General Services Officer was designated) to: (i) render a Report on Local Road Network and Road Map; (ii) regularly maintain and update the Registry of Public Infrastructures for Roads; and (iii) keep a complete Local Road Network Property Card for all roads and its components;

The Municipal Engineer to provide the OIC-Municipal Accountant and the Acting Municipal Treasurer with the complete description and cost segregation of road components for road projects; and

The OIC-Municipal Accountant to: (i) prepare the JEV to record the beginning balance of the local road network and its components; (ii) prepare and maintain a Local Road Network Ledger Card; (iii) keep and maintain subsidiary records for roads and road components for every road network, and (iii) prepare a lapsing schedule for the computation of the depreciation for each component at the end of the year.

We recommended that Management: 

Require the refund of the amount of ₱308,000.00 without prejudice to the limitation of appropriate legal sanctions against erring officials/employees;

Demand explanation from the AGDB why said checks were encashed and/or debited from the LGU account without the Accountant’s Advice otherwise hold the AGDB liable for the loss; 

Ensure that all claims against LGU funds must be supported with complete documents appearing legal, valid and proper;

Strictly observe fiscal responsibility to avoid loss or wastage of government funds; and

We recommended that Management direct the officers concerned to:
Maintain Supplies Ledger Cards (SLC), Subsidiary Ledgers (SL), and Stock Cards for inventory accounts;
Use Requisition and Issue Slip (RIS) and consolidate them weekly in the Summary of Supplies and Materials Issued (SSMI) for the issued supplies and materials to be used as basis for recording issued and ending inventory amounts;
Conduct the semi-annual physical inventory of all supplies and materials inventory of the LGU and prepare the report thereon, copy furnished the Auditor within the prescribed period;
Provide a stock room for proper storage of items of inventories; and
Submit updated reports on the utilization of the construction materials for proper recording to related accounts to reflect accurate balances.
We likewise recommended that Management designate an employee who will be in charge of monitoring the receipt and issuance/utilization of supplies and materials and other related control procedures of inventories as enjoined by the rules.
The Management was amenable to the audit recommendations.

We recommended that Management: 

Provide a stock room for proper storage of items of inventories; 

Require the Inventory Committee to conduct the semi-annual physical inventory of all supplies and materials inventory of the LGU and to prepare the report thereon, copy furnished the Auditor within the prescribed period; 
Direct the OIC-Municipal Accountant to maintain Subsidiary Ledger Cards and Subsidiary Ledgers for the Inventory accounts; and 

Instruct the Municipal Engineer to submit updated reports on the utilization of the construction materials for the infrastructure projects implemented by Administration.

We recommended that Management instruct:

The Inventory Committee to conduct an inventory of the local roads under the jurisdiction of the municipality and render a Report on the Physical count of the Road Networks System;


The Acting Municipal Treasurer (where no General Services Officer was designated) to: (a) render a Report on Local Road Network and Road Map; (b) regularly maintain and update the Registry of Public Infrastructures for Roads; and (c) keep a complete Local Road Network Property Card for all roads and its components;

The Municipal Engineer to provide the OIC-Municipal Accountant and the Acting Municipal Treasurer with the complete description and cost segregation of road components for road projects; and

The OIC-Municipal Accountant to: (a) prepare the JEV to record the beginning balance of the local road network and its components; (b) prepare and maintain a Local Road Network Ledger Card; (c) keep and maintain subsidiary records for roads and road components for every road network, and (d) prepare a lapsing schedule for the computation of the depreciation for each component at the end of the year.

We recommended that Management:

Instruct the officers/personnel involved in the procurement process to plan their activities including the probable goods and services that will be utilized and incorporate them in the Annual Procurement Plan;

Adhere strictly with Section 2 of COA Circular No. 97-002 as well as the procurement rules and procedures of the Revised IRR of RA 9184 and strengthen the internal control system on procurements;

Make use of petty cash fund to cover purchases involving small amounts for ordinary and essential needs of the Municipality; and

Utilize the alternative modes of procurement prescribed under Sections 48 to 53 of the IRR of RA 9184, if warranted, ensuring that checks for payments will be drawn only once the goods/services were already delivered/rendered and the procurement process is completely undertaken.

Re-establish and reinforce the deputation of barangay officials to aid the LGU in collecting taxes by setting their specific functions and responsibilities;

Create new positions and provide capable personnel who shall be in-charge with the issuance of Notice of Delinquencies (NOD) and the monitoring of the delinquent tax payers; and

Intensify the tax campaigns by sending treasury personnel to barangay especially during barangay assemblies for tax information drive in order to invite more taxpayers to pay taxes on time.

Require the refund of the amount of ₱308,000.00 without prejudice to the limitation of appropriate legal sanctions against erring officials/employees;

Demand explanation from the AGDB why said checks were encashed and/or debited from the LGU account without the Accountant’s Advice otherwise hold the AGDB liable for the loss; 

Ensure that all claims against LGU funds must be supported with complete documents appearing legal, valid and proper;

Strictly observe fiscal responsibility to avoid loss or wastage of government funds; and 

Change the authorized depository bank from PVB to LBP or DBP in order to preserve the interest of the Municipality, otherwise request authority from DOF.

