demand the immediate deposit of the amount of ₱2,385,627.73 otherwise file appropriate criminal and administrative charges against all other erring accountable officers; relieve them of their functions involving money matters at once; and withhold the payment of salaries to cover for the undeposited collections;
order all collectors to remit collections intact to the Municipal Treasurer (MT) before the end of the day;
require the MT to deposit all collections on the next banking day to the authorized depository bank and enforce strictly existing rules and regulations on the handling of collections and deposits;
direct that the RCDs must bear the date of remittance by the collector and the date the remittance was acknowledged/received by the MT; and
direct that collections and deposits be chronologically recorded in the summary report of collections and deposits prepared by the MT and the Cash Receipt Journal prepared by the accounting office.
